Wash and dry all produce.

Finely dice @Roma tomato{1}(finely diced). Trim and thinly slice 
@scallions{2}(thinly sliced). Halve @lime{1}. Halve, peel, and thinly slice 
@yellow onion{1}(thinly sliced). Core, deseed, and dice @poblano pepper{1}(diced 
into ½-inch pieces). Drain @black beans{13.4%ounce} over a #small bowl{}, 
reserving liquid.

In a separate small bowl, combine tomato, scallions, a big squeeze of lime 
juice, and a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{4%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high 
heat. Add onion and poblano; cook until just softened, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Add @southwest spice blend{1%tablespoon} and half the beans (you'll use the 
rest in the next step). Cook, stirring, until fragrant and warmed through, 
~{2-3%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper. Remove pan from heat.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add 
remaining beans and cook, stirring, until slightly softened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add ¼ cup reserved bean liquid (½ cup for 4 servings). Simmer until warmed 
through, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Reduce heat to low and stir in @butter{1%tablespoon}.

Remove pot from heat; mash beans until mostly smooth using a #potato masher{}. 
Season with plenty of salt and pepper.

Spread @flour tortillas{6} with mashed beans. Place a small amount of filling 
on one half of each tortilla, then sprinkle with @pepper jack cheese{1/2%cup} 
(diced).

Roll up tortillas, starting with filled side, and place seam sides down on a 
#plate{}.

Wash out pan used for filling.

Heat a large drizzle of oil in same pan over medium-high heat. Add flautas 
seam sides down. Cook, carefully turning so they stay intact, until golden 
brown and crispy, ~{1-2%minutes} per side.

> Work in batches if necessary and watch carefully to avoid burning.

Divide flautas between plates and top with @guacamole{4%tablespoon}, pico de 
gallo, @sour cream{4%tablespoon}, and @hot sauce{1%tsp}. (Alternatively, serve 
with toppings on the side for dipping.) Cut remaining lime into wedges and 
serve on the side.